    "minides": "The most legendary production 4WD on earth — the LC300 pairs a 309 hp twin-turbo V6 diesel with a new TNGA-F platform, 10-speed automatic, Toyota Safety Sense 3.0, and the GR-S adding front + rear differential locks.",
    "description": "The seventh-generation Land Cruiser LC300 (J300) launched in India in 2022, with the facelifted 2025 version following in February 2025 at ₹2.31 crore. India offers two variants — ZX and GR-S — both powered by a 3.3L twin-turbocharged V6 diesel (309 hp / 700 Nm) mated to a 10-speed automatic. The TNGA-F platform is 200 kg lighter and stiffer than its predecessor. ZX is the luxury-grade variant with 12.3-inch touchscreen, 14-speaker JBL audio, ventilated seats, 360-degree panoramic monitor, four-zone climate control, heads-up display, adaptive variable suspension (AVS), and Toyota Safety Sense 3.0 (Level 2 ADAS). The GR-S adds front and rear differential locks, a limited-slip rear differential, crawl control, GR badging, black exterior accents, an off-road tuned suspension, and the four-camera off-road monitor."
  },
